<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9707] InsertField.Key transformation should apply to tombstone records</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9707</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note: This was an inadvertent regression caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8523&quot; title=&quot;InsertField transformation fails when encountering tombstone event&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8523&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8523&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reproduction steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Configure an InsertField.Key transformation&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pass a tombstone record (with non-null key, but null value) through the transform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Expected behavior:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The key field is inserted, and the value remains null&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Observed behavior:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The key field is not inserted, and the value remains null&lt;/p&gt;</description>
